deck: King Peter Jason Quill of the remnant Spartax Empire in the 31st century
description:
Origin

Peter was born on Spartax in the year 2985. He would later become the Star-Lord and King of the Spartax Empire.

When a time anomaly was threatening the universe, he was sent by the Galactic Council to meet with the Guardians of the Galaxy. Together they traveled back in time to 2015 where he met the Star-Lord of that time. Despite being born 100 years after him, Starhawk revealed that he was actually his great-great-grandfather.

deck: Daughter of Metamorpho and one of the pampered heroes from earth 16.
description:
Sapphire "Saffi" Mason aka Megamorpho was the daughter of Metamorpho and Sapphire Stagg in earth 16. She was one of the pampered generation superhumans in a world where there were no crimes and the world troubles were solved by the Superman robots.

Saffi was the first victim of the attack of the Gentry who induced her to suicide, just in the middle of a talk with her friend Sister Miracle. In the autopsy of her fragmented corpse, Bloodwynd and Menta would discovered pieces from the mysterious event. Her death would alert Batman jr about the danger menacing the unsuspected earth 16.

deck: House cleaner who is secretly a golddigger.
description:
Origin

Cindy is originally a house cleaner, but hates cleaning windows. She uses her job as a house cleaner to get to rich customers. She tried to trick Lambik, but when she discovered that Jerom had joined a circus group called The Freaks and became world famous for his tricks, she dumped Lambik and tried to hook up with Jerom. When the double crossing came out, she confessed to being a golddigger. For punishment, The Freaks, who are secrelt aliens from the planet Xorodar took her to another planet, one completely covered in glass (remember she hates cleaning windows?).
name: Cindy

deck: Neuzel is an alien who crashed on Earth and posed as a member of a circus group called The Freaks.
description:
Origin

An alien from the planet Xorodar, he and his crew research other life forms in the galaxy. When they came close to Earth, they tried to study humans. During a reconnaissance flight in the hemisphere, their motor got hit by lightning. They crash landed and tried to repair their motor, but they couldn't. The outer casing of their motor is made of gold. Posing as circus freaks (because of their looks), they tried to raise enough money to buy gold for their motor. They succeeded only when Jerom joined their group and made them world famous. With enough gold, they repaired their motor and went back to their planet.
name: Neuzel

deck: King of the Road Knights
description:
Origin

Clint Curtis was a teenage racing enthusiast who along with his friends comprised the Road Knights who spent all their free time building, repairing and racing hot rods.

Seriously that was the characters raison d'etre, and in more than 20 years it never changed.

Creators

Introduced in the first hot rod themed comic Hot Rod Comics from Fawcett, he was featured in that for it's first seven issues until it was dropped, he returned in Hot Rods and Racing Cars # 42 where he stayed as the star until it's end with issue # 120.
name: Clint Curtis

deck: A specially bred gigantic Atlantean berserker warrior from the days of old, hybernating in the ocean and awakened by Aquaman to fight the Plura crisis.
description:
Origin

A gigantic and monstrous, specially bred Atlantean warrior, Devilfish was awakened by Aquaman as muscle for his own Justice League of Atlantis during the invasion of the Plura intelligence.

Creation

Devilfish was created by Len Kaminski and Javier Saltares. His first appearance was in Justice Leagues: Justice League of Atlantis #1.

Major Story Arcs

Justice Leagues: Justice League of Atlantis

During the time that the JLA was manipulated into splitting and forgetting by the Advance Man, Aquaman discovered some alien technological structures on islands in the ocean and in response he created the Justice League of Atlantis to confront the problem.

Following advice by Arion he awakened Devilfish, who at first, gladly joined the team. During their scouting mission though the team didn't follow the plan and charged to the alien tower completley obliterating it without finding out who is responsible.

Devilfish shortly after left the team, saying he wanted to follow someone who would provide constant chance for battle.

Justice Leagues: JLA

It's revealed that Devilfish had joined the Advance Man and his mission was to protect the Advance Man's client Plura while she was preparing on the bottom of the ocean.

The reawakened JLA though confronted them and defeated them, thus ending their plans for world domination.

Powers & Abilities

Devilfish is an ancient special breed of Atlantean berserker warrior and possesses a very high degree of physical power. He is gigantic and his lower body concludes to a tale, suited for life underwater.

Superhuman Strength / Berserker Strength

Devilfish possesses extreme superhuman strength. Arion says he possesses brute strength that surpasses imagining and he can be seen tearing apart a huge alien tower with his bare hands as if it was nothing. He can also casually take out a cyborg orca whale with one hit.

His strength increases even more when he is enraged.

Superhuman Durability

He has superhuman durability allowing him to take energy blasts directly without stopping him.

Enhanced Speed (Swimming)

He can swim at superhuman speeds, like all the members of JLAtlantis.

Enhanced Sences

He can see in darkness and at the bottom of the ocean. His smell is also superhuman.

Underwater Adaptation

He can function normally underwater and is able to withstand the high pressures and extreme temperatures of the deep. He can also breath out of water.

Claws

He possesses claws in his hands strong enough to tear through the flesh and metalic parts of a cyborg or an alien structure.

Longevity

He has lived since the days of ancient Atlantis.

Trained Warrior

Devilfish was bred for battle and is a special type of Atlantean Warrior, fighting with his bare hands and claws, usually ripping through his target.

deck: A First-Class Seaman who survived a deadly shipwreck and found himself on Dagger Island. He was mistaken to be a God by the native peoples due to his Navy outfit and equipment.
description:
Origin

Eddie Doyle made his first appearance in My Greatest Adventure #1 - My Cargo Was Death. He appeared in the short story titled I Was King of Dagger Island.

Creation

Eddie Doyle is thought to have been created by John Prentice and Leonard Starr.

Major Story Arcs

I Was King of Dagger Island

Eddie Doyle is a member of the United States Navy and is a First-Class Seaman. He was traveling to the Palu Island alongside Lieutenant Howell in the year 1944. The ship that Doyle was on was hit by a barrage of enemy torpedoes thus causing the ship to sink resulting in the deaths of everyone but Doyle and Howell.

When Doyle awoke from the concussion he received during the attack he found himself near a tropical island, this island was known as Dagger Island. He carried the unconscious body of Howell to shore where they were greeted by a band of local natives. Doyle had prepared to fight the natives but was taken by surprise when they thought him to be a deity, this was because of his 'Frog-Suit' that he had been wearing.

Doyle gained the trust of the natives and enjoyed living in a life of luxury for a short period of time; however, Howell wanted to return to their original mission and wound up knocking Doyle out. When Doyle woke back up he was on a U.S. Navy vessel and none of his fellow seamen believed his tale as the king of Dagger Island.

Powers & Abilities

Eddie Doyle has no superpowers; however, he has a basic level of Navy Training and an above-average swimming ability.
name: Eddie Doyle

deck: Lieutenant Howell was the survivor of a shipwreck who awoke on Dagger Island. He pretended to be a slave for Eric Dowell in order to fool the natives of the island.
description:
Origin

Lieutenant Howell was first seen in My Greatest Adventure #1 - My Cargo Was Death. He appeared in a short story titled I Was King of Dagger Island.

Creation

Lieutenant Howell is thought to have been created by John Prentice and Leonard Starr.

Character Evolution

Lieutenant Howell is a sensible and strong leader; however, he eventually turns against his own partner, Eddie Doyle, and knocks him out.

Major Story Arcs

I Was King of Dagger Island

Lieutenant Howell is in charge of a U.S. Navy vessel and is preparing his frog suit when the ship hits a series of hidden mines. The resulting explosions causes the ship to sink and sends Howell into a concussion, thankfully Howell is saved by a First-Class Seaman named Eddie Doyle.

The two arrive on a nearby island and are met by a group of strange natives. The natives believe Doyle to be some sort of deity and think Howell is his slave. The two of them keep this act up in order to gain the trust of the natives.

Not wanting to pretend to be Doyle's slave for the rest of his life he ends up knocking Doyle out and bringing him to a nearby boat.

Powers & Abilities

Lieutenant Howell has no superpowers; however, he has received basic Navy training from the U.S. Navy.
name: Lieutenant Howell

deck: John Marston is a pilot who was a U.F.O. while flying in a plane one night. Riddled with curiosity he spent all of his free time trying to find proof of the object while looking for aliens.
description:
Origin

John Marston was first seen in My Greatest Adventure #1 - My Cargo Was Death. He appeared in the short story titled I Hunted a Flying Saucer!

Creation

John Marston was created by Will Ely.

Character Evolution

Marston originally was an average man who had come across a flying saucer. Unfortunately Marston's mental state began to deteriorate when those around him didn't believe his claims about his findings, thus resulting in an overall mental breakdown.

Major Story Arcs

I Hunted a Flying Saucer

John Marston was flying a plane late at night when he observed a bright object fly past his plane; clipping it's wing slightly, thus causing Marston's plane to spiral downwards resulting in a crashed landing, thankfully Marston survived.

With new-found knowledge of a strange U.F.O. Marston went to the Civil Air Patrol Officials to report his observations; however, the two officers that met with Marston didn't believe him and thought him to be a loon. Marston eventually met with a man named Mr. Dennings who was a member of the Air Force who is assigned to a project known as "Blue Sky" in which he must locate any and all clues related to U.F.O.s.

Marston ventured out on Mr. Denning's orders to locate the U.F.O. He found the object which was revealed to be an alien ship from outer space. Marston took a picture of the ship which caused the aliens to lose their trust in him. Marston brought the picture and a piece of metal he found at the scene back to Mr. Dennings; however, the photo turned up blank and the metal had been transformed to dust.

When Marston brought Mr. Dennings to the location of the alien ship the area appeared untouched, even though there was a crater there when Marston found the ship. As a last resort Marston was hooked up to a lie detector and asked if he saw a flying saucer, to which he responded yes. Unfortunately for Marston the lie detector claimed he was lying and Marston was sent away by Mr. Dennings.

Due to the toll this event took on Marston's mind he ended up flying his plane high into the sky and was never seen again.

Powers & Abilities

Marston had no superpowers; however, he had the ability to pilot an airplane.
name: John Marston
